  "decisions": [
    {
      "decision": "{\"note\":\"analyze re-run after tasks: 0 CRITICAL/HIGH. Prior F1 gate-facet concern RESOLVED (spec now names both source.mnemonic-vs-positional and source.casing, matching contract invariant #4). Remediated 5 findings in tasks.md/quickstart.md: G2 added SC-002 test T038; G1/G3 added FR-011+SC-003 test T039; U1 added D4 fixture-only guard to T003/T014; N1 added Article-IV debounce caution to T026; I2 added source.casing to quickstart Scenario 4. Cleared to /speckit-implement.\",\"step\":\"analyze\"}"
    },
    {
      "decision": "encoding-spelling migration IR-observable half is the modifier fold (LCTRL/RCTRL->CTRL); pure quoted-literal<->u-notation is a semantic identity at the IR level",
      "why": "the codec canonicalizes char spelling on emit (BMP chars always render as U+XXXX), so char-spelling normalization is not IR-observable; the source-diff is rendered separately for the preview",
      "rejected": "mutating char nodes for spelling (no-op, since IR already canonical)"
    },
    {
      "decision": "compile-regression gate checks compile().success in addition to oracle error/fatal severity",
      "why": "validateWithOracle only emits hint/warning for broken keyboards (undefined group, undeclared store); compile().success is the reliable blocking signal",
      "rejected": "oracle-severity-only gate (would let compile-breaking transforms commit)"
    },
    {
      "decision": "verify.ts dynamic-imports the simulator",
      "why": "the Node-only simulator vendor uses bare import specifiers Vite cannot resolve; a static import dragged it into the studio bundle via the engine barrel",
      "rejected": "static top-level import of simulate (breaks studio build/tests)"
    }
  ],
